    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Describe your issue\r\n\r\nConsider following code:\r\n\r\n```cython\r\ncdef int bar(int a, int b) nogil:\r\n    a + b\r\n\r\nwith nogil:\r\n    bar(3, 5)\r\n\r\nbar(3, 5)\r\n\r\ncdef void bar2(int a, int b) nogil:\r\n    a + b\r\n\r\nwith nogil:\r\n    bar2(3, 5)\r\n\r\nbar2(3, 5)\r\n```\r\n\r\nCython incorrectly highlights error handling code which contains characters escaped in HTML (`&` in the case of example below). It is because Cython does regex matching using already HTML escaped text and escaped characters contains `;`:\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/cython/cython/assets/827060/0b7768c6-9f39-4a45-9716-1fcf4ac3a179)\r\n\r\n## Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nCode is correctly highlighted:\r\n![image](https://github.com/cython/cython/assets/827060/4be3fb05-98c3-4e80-86e6-ef13c928e914)\r\n\r\n## OS\r\nNo response\r\n\r\n## Python version\r\nNo response\r\n\r\n## Cython version\r\nMost recent master",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "The issue is that regex responsible for detecting error handling code \r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/cython/cython/blob/8892b021a3ceee623abccc0bfe1c705952c125f1/Cython/Compiler/Annotate.py#L318\r\n\r\ncannot handle escaped characters (to be precise this part: `[^;]*`) - e.g. `&amp;`",
